item.title: Embracing Consistency: A One-Stage Approach for Spatio-Temporal Video Grounding

item.title: SuperYOLO: Super Resolution Assisted Object Detection in Multimodal Remote Sensing Imagery

item.title: StyleMask: Disentangling the Style Space of StyleGAN2 for Neural Face Reenactment
item.description: In this paper we address the problem of neural face reenactment, where, given a pair of a source and a target facial image, we need to transfer the target's pose (defined as the head pose and its facial expressions) to the source image, by preserving at the same time the source's identity characteristics (e. g., facial shape, hair style, etc), even in the challenging case where the source and the target faces belong to different identities.
